column5: Can anyone tell me what the current water temps are on Gullrock. I see a low of 33 tonight and hoping we will see sub 60 water temperatures next week. Thanks Pat T

will be there sat the 24th. hoping for stable, solid weather. looks like rain all day sat and then decent temps other than like 50 as high on wed. i believe. 55 to 60 is not bad for high temps. high winds can stay away. haha.
When I got to Savant on the 10th it was 63 and when I left on the 17th it was 58 and Savant is a lot bigger than Gullrock. Good luck and fish were anywhere from 8-28’
Those lakes are also like 300 miles apart.
You’re welcome. It’s a hobby of mine.
